President Trump gave remarks during his visit to India, praising Prime Minister Modi and the strong relationship between the two countries. He discussed the coronavirus outbreak, stating that the US is in good shape and China is working hard to control the virus. President Trump also mentioned the recent stock market drop and expressed confidence that the market will bounce back. He took questions from business leaders, who shared their investments and praised his policies, particularly tax cuts and deregulation. The President highlighted the importance of the steel and aluminum industries and the benefits of his trade deals. He concluded by expressing his support for the agricultural sector and his commitment to creating jobs in the US.